The Pharisees said to Jesus, "Look, your disciples are doing what is unlawful on the Sabbath."
He replied, "Have you never read what David did? He and his men were hungry. They needed food.
That was in the days of Abiathar the high priest. David went into the house of God, and ate the shewbread, which was lawful only for the priests to eat. And he gave also to his companions.
Then Jesus said to them, "The Sabbath was made for man, not man for the Sabbath."
