Once Jesus entered the temple. There was a man with a withered and crooked hand.
Some Pharisees were trying to find fault with Jesus. They were watching him closely. They wanted to see if he would heal the man on the Sabbath.
Jesus spoke to the man who had a withered and paralyzed hand. He said to him, "Stand up in front of everyone."
Then Jesus said to them, "What does the law say we should do on the Sabbath? Make it a day for good deeds or for evil? To save life or to destroy it?" But they remained silent.
Jesus saw the people and was indignant. He was displeased with them because their hearts were hardened. Then he said to the man, "Stretch out your hand." So he did, and his hand was restored as good as new.
